==English==

===Etymology===
{{It.}} ''[[presto]]'' "quickly"

===Pronunciation===
*''[[RP]]:'' {{IPA|/ˈprɛstəʊ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"prEst@U/}}
*''US:'' {{AHD|prĕs'tō}}, {{IPA|/ˈprɛstoʊ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"prEstoU/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛstəʊ|-ɛstəʊ]]

===Adverb===
'''presto'''

# {{music}} Very fast or quickly; a directive for the musician(s) to play in a very quick [[tempo]].

===Interjection===
'''presto!'''

# Used by [[magician]]s when performing a [[trick]].
#: ''So I put my hand into the hat and '''presto'''! Out comes a rabbit!''

====Translations====
{{top}}
{{mid}}
*Portuguese: [[pronto]]!
{{bottom}}

====Derived terms====
*[[hey presto]]

